CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Department of Aging – Aging Services – Program Repeal and Consolidation
3 FOR the purpose of repealing provisions of law requiring the Secretary of Aging to develop
4 certain congregate housing and assisted living programs for seniors; repealing the
5 Interagency Committee on Aging Services and transferring certain responsibilities
6 of the Committee to the Department of Aging; authorizing the Department to
7 perform certain duties to implement and coordinate services to older adults and to
8 collaborate with certain entities that establish local interagency committees;
9 requiring the Department to establish, coordinate, and supervise a program to
10 provide single points of entry within each planning and service area; authorizing
11 area agencies on aging to make agreements with certain entities and provide staff at
12 the single points of entry for certain purposes; requiring the Department to develop,
13 coordinate, and administer with area agencies on aging or other persons a certain
14 system to provide certain services to certain older adults; requiring the Department
15 to engage with key stakeholders to conduct certain transition planning and to
16 provide certain services to certain older adults; and generally relating to the
17 Department of Aging and aging services.
