12 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That, beginning in June 2025, the
13 Department of Aging shall engage with key stakeholders, including area agencies on aging,
14 to:
15 (1) conduct program transition planning and to co–design the new,
16 consolidated program required under Section 1 of this Act; and
17 (2) provide that individuals enrolled in the Senior Care, Senior Assisted
18 Living Subsidy, and Congregate Housing Services Programs at the time of the transition
19 required under Section 1 of this Act will receive a person–centered assessment, performed
20 by the appropriate area agency on aging for that jurisdiction, to determine an individual
21 transition plan that may include continued service delivery, or an alternative to ensure
22 appropriate care is maintained.
